title: For Sale:  Arisaka Type 38
postcontent:
For sale/trade is a Arisaka type 38 service rifle that was brought back from a tour during WWII. I do not know exact details of where this was accquired but I know this is not a surplus or a training model. The man who brought it back from the war gave it to his son (family friend) who passed it on to my father and eventually my father gifted it to me. My father had shot it a small amount when he was a teenager but it has not been used for decades. I have given the gun a quick once over to keep it clean and happy, I wouldnt hesitate to shoot it today. If this doesnt sell I will most likely sporterize it for big game.
The Imperial Chrysanthemum and all serial numbers are in perfect legible shape.
The stock is a little beat up from war service, not storage or post war use.
There is only one place that has any rust which is the end of the barrel and it is very superficial/light.
The action of the bolt and pin are still very solid and smooth.
All original components, no modifications.
As far as a trade I am interested in a small CCW style handgun 380/9mm. I am also interested in Jeep ZJ 98' compatible suspension components for up to 3'' lift and/or tires in good shape for 15''wheels 5x4.5 lug pattern.
Let me know if you have more questions or would like more pictures, thanks for looking!

It's older (2002) but has surprisingly crisp lands and grooves.  It's been carried a lot, and at some point developed some minor corrosion on the slide, mostly on the cerrations on the left side (I'm told this is very common with these guns, and due to perspiration).
